    <div class="container">
        <header>
            <h1>CSS Tutorial</h1>
            <p class="subtitle">Learn CSS styling with interactive examples</p>
        </header>
        
        <div class="nav">
            <div class="nav-item active">Basics</div>
            <div class="nav-item">Layout</div>
            <div class="nav-item">Responsive</div>
            <div class="nav-item">Effects</div>
            <div class="nav-item">Practice</div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="content">
            <div class="card">
                <h2>What is CSS?</h2>
                <p>CSS (Cascading Style Sheets) is used to style and layout web pages. It allows you to control the presentation of HTML elements, including colors, spacing, fonts, and more.</p>
                
                <div class="example">
                    <pre><span class="comment">/* This is a CSS comment */</span>
<span class="selector">body</span> {
  <span class="property">background-color</span>: <span class="value">#1a202c</span>;
  <span class="property">color</span>: <span class="value">#e2e8f0</span>;
  <span class="property">font-family</span>: <span class="value">'Segoe UI', Tahoma, sans-serif</span>;
}

<span class="selector">.container</span> {
  <span class="property">max-width</span>: <span class="value">1200px</span>;
  <span class="property">margin</span>: <span class="value">0 auto</span>;
  <span class="property">padding</span>: <span class="value">20px</span>;
}</pre>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="card">
                <h2>CSS Selectors</h2>
                <p>Selectors are patterns used to select the element(s) you want to style. There are several types of selectors:</p>
                
                <div class="example">
                    <pre><span class="comment">/* Element selector */</span>
<span class="selector">p</span> {
  <span class="property">color</span>: <span class="value">blue</span>;
}

<span class="comment">/* Class selector */</span>
<span class="selector">.highlight</span> {
  <span class="property">background-color</span>: <span class="value">yellow</span>;
}

<span class="comment">/* ID selector */</span>
<span class="selector">#header</span> {
  <span class="property">font-size</span>: <span class="value">2rem</span>;
}

<span class="comment">/* Attribute selector */</span>
<span class="selector">a[target="_blank"]</span> {
  <span class="property">color</span>: <span class="value">red</span>;
}</pre>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="card">
                <h2>Box Model</h2>
                <p>The CSS box model describes the rectangular boxes generated for elements. It includes content, padding, border, and margin.</p>
                
                <div class="visual-example">
                    <div class="example-element">Content</div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="example">
                    <pre><span class="selector">.box</span> {
  <span class="comment">/* Content dimensions */</span>
  <span class="property">width</span>: <span class="value">300px</span>;
  <span class="property">height</span>: <span class="value">200px</span>;
  
  <span class="comment">/* Padding - space inside the border */</span>
  <span class="property">padding</span>: <span class="value">20px</span>;
  
  <span class="comment">/* Border - around the padding */</span>
  <span class="property">border</span>: <span class="value">2px solid #3182ce</span>;
  
  <span class="comment">/* Margin - space outside the border */</span>
  <span class="property">margin</span>: <span class="value">30px</span>;
  
  <span class="comment">/* Total element width = width + padding + border + margin */</span>
}</pre>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="card">
                <h2>Flexbox Layout</h2>
                <p>Flexbox is a CSS layout module that makes it easier to design flexible and responsive layout structures.</p>
                
                <div class="visual-example">
                    <div class="example-element">1</div>
                    <div class="example-element">2</div>
                    <div class="example-element">3</div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="example">
                    <pre><span class="selector">.container</span> {
  <span class="property">display</span>: <span class="value">flex</span>;
  <span class="property">justify-content</span>: <span class="value">space-between</span>;
  <span class="property">align-items</span>: <span class="value">center</span>;
  <span class="property">flex-wrap</span>: <span class="value">wrap</span>;
}

<span class="selector">.item</span> {
  <span class="property">flex</span>: <span class="value">1 0 200px</span>;
  <span class="property">margin</span>: <span class="value">10px</span>;
}</pre>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="card">
                <h2>CSS Transitions</h2>
                <p>Transitions enable you to change property values smoothly over a given duration.</p>
                
                <div class="visual-example">
                    <div class="example-element" id="transition-example">Hover Me</div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="example">
                    <pre><span class="selector">.button</span> {
  <span class="property">background-color</span>: <span class="value">#3182ce</span>;
  <span class="property">color</span>: <span class="value">white</span>;
  <span class="property">padding</span>: <span class="value">10px 20px</span>;
  <span class="property">border-radius</span>: <span class="value">5px</span>;
  <span class="property">transition</span>: <span class="value">all 0.3s ease</span>;
}

<span class="selector">.button:hover</span> {
  <span class="property">background-color</span>: <span class="value">#63b3ed</span>;
  <span class="property">transform</span>: <span class="value">translateY(-3px)</span>;
  <span class="property">box-shadow</span>: <span class="value">0 4px 6px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1)</span>;
}</pre>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="card">
                <h2>Try it Yourself</h2>
                <p>Write your CSS code in the editor below and see how it affects the HTML element.</p>
                
                <div class="try-it">
                    <div class="editor-container">
                        <div class="editor">
                            <h4>HTML</h4>
                            <textarea id="html-editor"><div id="target-element">
  <h3>Styled Element</h3>
  <p>This is a sample element that you can style with CSS.</p>
  <button>Click Me</button>
</div></textarea>
                        </div>
                        <div class="editor">
                            <h4>CSS</h4>
                            <textarea id="css-editor">#target-element {
  background-color: #2d3748;
  padding: 20px;
  border-radius: 10px;
  color: #e2e8f0;
  font-family: 'Segoe UI', Tahoma, sans-serif;
}

#target-element h3 {
  color: #63b3ed;
  margin-bottom: 10px;
}

#target-element p {
  line-height: 1.6;
  margin-bottom: 15px;
}

#target-element button {
  background-color: #3182ce;
  color: white;
  border: none;
  padding: 8px 16px;
  border-radius: 5px;
  cursor: pointer;
}

#target-element button:hover {
  background-color: #63b3ed;
}</textarea>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <button onclick="applyStyles()">Apply Styles</button>
                    <button onclick="resetStyles()">Reset</button>
                    
                    <h4>Result:</h4>
                    <div class="result" id="css-result"></div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="hint">
                    <p><strong>Hint:</strong> Try changing these properties:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>background-color, color</li>
                        <li>padding, margin, border</li>
                        <li>font-size, font-family
